al engineering department at a public university in the Chicago metropolitan area  this program provides unique opportunities for students to interact with world class industries through research projects and internship programs All College of Engineering undergraduate students are required to be advised before they are able to register for classes each semester  Advising hold will not be removed until you are advised  Sign up is required for Advising and takes place during the  th week of the semester  Advising for Chemical Engineering Students is during the   th week of instruction Apply now GETTING STARTED Undergraduate Admissions    information on how to apply to the College of Engineering Undergraduate Admissions  Undergraduate Catalog    Chemical Engineering program requirements and course offerings Undergraduate Catalog  Frequently Asked Questions  Frequently Asked Questions  DEGREE REQUIREMENTS  nDegree Requirements n Degree Requirements Curriculum Flowchart  n Sample Semester Course Schedule n  Sample Semester Course Schedule SPECIAL PROGRAMS  nChemical Engineering for Pre Med Students n Chemical Engineering for Pre Med Students  nHonors College n Honors College UNDERGRADUATE FORMS Change of Major Modification of Major  nProposal for Undergraduate Research n Proposal for Undergraduate Research  nUndergraduate Student General Petition n Undergraduate Student General Petition  nIntercollege Transfer Petition n Intercollege Transfer Petition  nGraduation Checklist n Graduation Checklist For more information  please visit the College of Engineering website College of Engineering OTHER IMPORTANT LINKS  nUniversity Degree Requirements n University Degree Requirements  nUndergraduate Course Descriptions n Undergraduate Course Descriptions  nUIC Schedule of Classes  n UIC Schedule of Classes   nAcademic Calendar  n Academic Calendar   r n    S Clinton St r nChicago  IL        r n    S Clinton St r nChicago  IL         cheuic uic edu               Future Students Un